---
source: tests/snapshot_tests.rs
expression: stdout
---
ssh-cli: lightweight one-shot binary (spawn→run→exit). Multi-host XDG storage without .env. Password
or key auth. No telemetry.

Usage: ssh-cli [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  vps           Manages registered VPS hosts
  connect       Sets the active VPS (writes sibling `active` file in the config directory)
  exec          Runs a command on the VPS over SSH (stdout/stderr captured)
  sudo-exec     Runs a command with `sudo` (safe `sh -c` packing)
  su-exec       Runs a command with one-shot `su -` elevation
  scp           SCP file transfer (upload/download)
  sftp          SFTP subsystem transfer and remote filesystem ops (G-SFTP)
  tunnel        SSH tunnel with mandatory deadline (bounded one-shot)
  health-check  Checks SSH connectivity to a VPS (or multi-host with `--all` / `--hosts`)
  secrets       Manages the primary key and at-rest secret encryption (one-shot)
  completions   Generates shell completions
  commands      Emits the full command tree as JSON (agent discovery / rules `mycli commands`)
  schema        Emits embedded JSON Schema catalog or one schema body (G-E2E-02)
  doctor        Root alias for `vps doctor` (XDG / schema diagnostics; G-E2E-03)
  locale        Diagnoses and manages UI language (locale resolution / XDG preference)
  tls           TLS stack: provider status, mTLS identities, ACME certs (XDG; rustls only)
  help          Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version

Global options:
      --lang <LOCALE>
          Forces the CLI language (BCP47; must negotiate to `en` or `pt-BR`).
          
          Examples: `en`, `en-US`, `pt-BR`, `pt`. Invalid tags fail clap validation.

  -v, --verbose
          Increases log verbosity on stderr

  -q, --quiet
          Suppresses non-JSON output (quiet mode)

      --config-dir <DIR>
          Configuration directory override (useful for tests)

      --no-color
          Disables colored output

      --output-format <OUTPUT_FORMAT>
          Global output format (text, json). If omitted: JSON when stdout is not a TTY

          Possible values:
          - text: Human-readable text (default)
          - json: Structured JSON

      --json
          Force JSON on stdout (agent; alias of `--output-format json`; G-AUD-01).
          
          Global — appears before or after subcommands. Subcommand fields use `from_global` so there
          is a single `--json` long name (clap uniqueness).

      --disable-sudo
          Disables sudo-exec/su-exec for this invocation (alias --disableSudo)

      --replace-host-key
          Replaces a diverging host key in TOFU known_hosts

      --allow-plaintext-secrets
          Allow plaintext secrets at rest (no auto `secrets.key`). Prefer for tests only

      --secrets-key-file <PATH>
          Path to a 64-hex primary-key file (overrides XDG `secrets.key` for this one-shot)

      --use-keyring
          Prefer OS keyring for the primary key (CLI flag only; no product env store)

      --timeout <MS>
          Global default timeout in milliseconds for SSH ops (exec/scp/health-check). Local
          `--timeout` on a subcommand wins. Tunnel still requires `--timeout-ms`

      --max-concurrency <N>
          Cap concurrent multi-host SSH sessions / tunnel forwards (1..=MAX_CONCURRENCY).
          
          Default: auto from CPUs × I/O oversubscribe vs free RAM (see `concurrency`). Applies to
          `--all` fan-out and tunnel accepts (no env store; G-UNSAFE-14).

      --fail-fast
          Stop admitting new multi-host units after the first failure (G-O1).
          
          Default: continue all hosts (agent-friendly partial success). In-flight units still
          finish; never-started hosts are omitted from batch results unless callers pad skipped
          rows.

      --scp-file-concurrency <N>
          Max concurrent SCP file transfers on **one** SSH session (G-O4).
          
          Default: 1 (serial multi-file, session reuse). Values >1 open parallel SCP channels on the
          same session (bounded). Env: not used; CLI only.

Examples:
  ssh-cli vps add --name prod --host h.example --user deploy --key ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
  printf '%s' "$PASS" | ssh-cli exec prod 'hostname' --json --password-stdin
  ssh-cli scp upload prod ./a.bin /tmp/a.bin --json
  ssh-cli tunnel prod 8080 127.0.0.1 80 --timeout-ms 60000 --json
  ssh-cli vps export -o /tmp/hosts.toml
